<div xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><p coords="1,105.20,328.18,423.83,9.96;1,65.20,338.48,463.98,9.96;1,65.20,348.88,464.63,9.96;1,65.20,359.18,464.20,9.96;1,65.20,369.58,464.33,9.96;1,65.20,379.88,464.43,9.96;1,65.20,390.28,284.12,9.96"><s coords="1,105.20,328.18,423.83,9.96">Ba2ScSbO6 (BSS) has been synthesized in polycrystalline form by solid state reaction at 1400 ˚C for 72 Hrs.</s><s coords="1,65.20,338.48,463.98,9.96;1,65.20,348.88,48.48,9.96">Structural characterization of the compound was done through X-ray diffraction (XRD) followed by Riedvelt analysis of the XRD pattern.</s><s coords="1,116.12,348.88,413.70,9.96;1,65.20,359.18,464.20,9.96;1,65.20,369.58,46.79,9.96">The crystal structure is cubic, space group Fm-3m (No. 225) with the lattice parameter, a = 8.230 Ǻ. Optical bandgap of the present system has been calculated using the UV-Vis Spectroscopy and Kubelka-Munk (KM) function, it's value being 4.2eV.</s><s coords="1,114.83,369.58,414.70,9.96;1,65.20,379.88,193.38,9.96">A detailed study of the electronic properties has also been carried out using the Full-Potential Linear Augmented Plane Wave (FPLAPW) as implemented in WIEN2k.</s><s coords="1,261.12,379.88,268.51,9.96;1,65.20,390.28,284.12,9.96">BSS is found to be a large band-gap insulator with potential technological applications, such as dielectric resonators and filers in microwave applications.</s></p></div>
